'''The Edelstein Center for Social Research''' is a Brazilian [[think tank]] based in [[Rio de Janeiro]], that: 1) promotes [[research]] and [[publication]]s designed to improve [[public policy|public policies]] and [[institution]]s to enhance [[democracy]] and [[social justice]] in [[Latin America]]; 2) fosters the dialogue between [[social actor]]s and knowledge producers to disseminate internationally Latin American [[social sciences]] production and research institutions; 3) develops free access [[virtual library|virtual libraries]], [[data bank]]s and the translation of Latin American [[social research]] works into English.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.centroedelstein.org.br/English/QuemSomos.asp |title=The Edelstein Center, About us |publisher=Centroedelstein.org.br |date= |accessdate=2012-03-08}}</ref>

== History and Staff ==

The '''Edelstein Center''' was established in 2004, by Joel Edelstein,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.centroedelstein.org.br/English/JoelEdelstein.asp |title=About Joel Edelstein |publisher=Centroedelstein.org.br |date= |accessdate=2012-03-08}}</ref> a USA citizen living in [[Brazil]]. From its inception is directed by [[Bernardo Sorj]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bernardosorj.com.br/english/index.asp |title=Director Bernardo Sorj’s site |publisher=Bernardosorj.com.br |date=2005-12-30 |accessdate=2012-03-08}}</ref> and the Board of Advisors includes [[Adama Samassékou]] (Mali), Angelina Peralva (France), Daniel Pécaut (France), Giorgio Alberti (Italy), [[Guillermo O'Donnell]] (in memoriam, Argentina), [[Jean-Michel Blanquer]] (France) [[:es:Julio Cotler|Julio Cotler]] (Peru), Sérgio Costa (Germany), Shepard Forman (United States) and [[Simon Schwartzman]] (Brazil).

In 2007, in association with the Instituto [[Fernando Henrique Cardoso]]<ref>[http://www.ifhc.org.br Instituto Fernando Henrique Cardoso]</ref> founded the ''Democratic Platform Project''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.plataformademocratica.org/English |title=Democratic Platform Project |publisher=Plataformademocratica.org |date= |accessdate=2012-03-08}}</ref>

In 2009-2010, the '''Edelstein Center''' was one of the sponsors of the [[Latin American Initiative on Drugs and Democracy]]. The other organizations were Instituto [[Fernando Henrique Cardoso]] and the [[Open Society Institute]].<ref name="drogasedemocracia">{{cite web|url=http://www.drogasedemocracia.org/English/Default.asp |title=Latin American Initiative on Drugs and Democracy |publisher=Drogasedemocracia.org |date= |accessdate=2012-03-08}}</ref>

In 2010-2011, the '''Edelstein Center''' was part of the secretariat of the [[Global Commission on Drug Policy]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.globalcommissionondrugs.org/ |title=The Global Commission on Drug Policy |publisher=Globalcommissionondrugs.org |date= |accessdate=2012-03-08}}</ref>

== Programs ==

'''The Information Society in Latin America'''

This research program concentrates on the impact of new [[information and communications technology]] on the transformation of [[Latin America]]'s education system, public space and democratic life.<ref>[SORJ, Bernardo. Information Societies and Digital Divides: an Introduction. Milano: Polimetrica. Rio de Janeiro: The Edelstein Center for Social Research, 2008. {{ISBN|9788876991288}}. http://www.centroedelstein.org.br/PDF/Information_Societies_and_Digital_Divides_ebook.pdf]</ref><ref>[REMOLD, Julie. Educational Technologies and Social Inequality in Brazilian Public Schools. Rio de Janeiro: The Edelstein Center for Social Research, Série E-book 1, 2006. {{ISBN|8599662198}}. http://www.centroedelstein.org.br/PDF/e-book01-port.pdf]</ref>
Recently the '''Edelstein Center''' has completed a research on the use of computers and [[Internet]] by public school teachers in [[Rio de Janeiro]].<ref>[SORJ, Bernardo; LISSOVSKY, Mauricio. Internet in Brazilian Public Schools: Policies beyond Politics. Rio de Janeiro: The Edelstein Center for Social Research, Working Paper nº 6, May 2011. http://www.centroedelstein.org.br/PDF/WP_6_English.pdf]</ref> The study indicates that even when they have a positive impact, they cannot be separated from the educational and human context. A comprehensive policy needs to properly training teachers, in particular confronting the difficulties of the older generation, use monitored software, and adequate maintaining the physical infrastructural and technical support for school computer labs.

'''Civil Society and Globalization Agendas'''

The ''Civil Society and Globalization Agendas'' research program focuses on the current changes in [[Latin America]]’s [[civil society]]. Civil society played an important role in the promotion of [[democracy]] during the period of [[military dictatorships]]. However, more recently, civil society organizations have expanded and changed profoundly. While continuing to play an important role in the defense of [[human rights]], in many countries civil society has become a vehicle for  political parties, individual politicians, unions and social movements to channel public funds for their own benefit and/or political cooptation.<ref>[SORJ, B. (org.). Usos, abusos y desafíos de la sociedad civil en América Latina. Buenos Aires: Siglo XX, 2010. {{ISBN|9789871013777}}. http://www.centroedelstein.org.br/PDF/Usos_abusos_y_desafios.pdf]</ref><ref>[SORJ, Bernardo. Civil Societies North-South Relations: NGOs and Dependency. Rio de Janeiro: The Edelstein Center for Social Research, Working Paper 1, 2005. {{ISBN|8599662023}}. http://www.centroedelstein.org.br/PDF/WorkingPapers/WP_1_English.pdf]</ref><ref>[SORJ, Bernardo OLIVEIRA, Miguel Darcy (Ed). Sociedad Civil y Democracia en América Latina: crisis y reinvención de la política. Rio de Janeiro: Centro Edelstein de Investigaciones Sociales São Paulo: iFHC, 2007. {{ISBN|9788599662205}}. http://www.centroedelstein.org.br/PDF/sociedadecivilydemocracia_LA.pdf]</ref>

'''Virtual Libraries'''

''[http://www.bvce.org The Edelstein Center Virtual Library of Human Sciences]'' develops and offers [[free access]] to a set of [[virtual library|virtual libraries]] with 55.000 titles in constant expansion. The virtual library includes: 1) [http://www.bvce.org/LivrosBrasileiros.asp Brazilian Books] which makes freely available re-editions of books already published by Brazilian authors or residents, in Portuguese as well as other languages, with 220 titles. 2) [http://www.bvce.org/SociedadeInformacao.asp The Information Society Library], with more than 30.000 academic texts about the [[information society]]. 3) [http://socialsciences.scielo.org SciELO Social Sciences English Edition], in partnerships with SciELO<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.scielo.org/php/index.php/ |title=SciELO (Scientific Electronic Library Online) |publisher=SciELO |date= |accessdate=2012-03-14}}</ref> contains 30 [[academic journal|journals]] from [[Brazil]] and other [[Latin America]]n countries translated into English. 4) [http://www.plataformademocratica.org/English/BuscaPublicacoes.aspx Plataforma Democrática Virtual Library] with 15.000 academic texts on [[democracy]] in [[Latin America]].

'''Democratic Platform'''

[http://www.plataformademocratica.org/English ''Plataforma Democrática''] is a joint initiative of the '''Edelstein Center''' and the '''Instituto [[Fernando Henrique Cardoso]]''' devoted to strengthening Latin American [[democracy|democratic]] [[institution]]s <ref>[O'DONNELL, Guillermo. Democracia, agência e Estado. Teoria com intenção comparativa. Rio de Janeiro: Paz e Terra, 2011. {{ISBN|9788577531455}}. http://www.centroedelstein.org.br/PDF/donnell_sumario.PDF]</ref><ref>[FAUSTO, Sérgio (comp.). Difícil democracia. Buenos Aires: Siglo XXI, 2010. {{ISBN|9789871013869}}. http://www.centroedelstein.org.br/PDF/Dificil_democracia_esp.pdf]</ref><ref>[SORJ, Bernardo MARTUCCELLI, Danilo. The Latin American Challenge: Social Cohesion and Democracy. São Paulo: Instituto Fernando Henrique Cardoso / Rio de Janeiro: The Edelstein Center for Social Research, 2008. {{ISBN|9788599662588}}. http://www.centroedelstein.org.br/PDF/TheLatinAmerican%20Challenge.pdf]</ref> and [[culture]] by fostering pluralistic debate on the social and political transformations of the region and the world. ''Plataforma Democrática'' includes 21 associated institutions in [[Latin America]]. Its current areas of [[research]] and policy papers are: '''a)''' ''Global Geopolitical Transformations and Latina America Democracies'';<ref>[Global Geopolitical Changes and the Future of Democracy in Latin America series  http://www.plataformademocratica.org/English/PublicacoesPlataforma.aspx#CambiosGeopoliticos]</ref><ref>[SORJ, Bernardo FAUSTO, Sergio (comps.). América Latina: Transformaciones geopolíticas y democracia. Buenos Aires: Siglo XXI, 2011. {{ISBN|9789871013944}}. http://www.centroedelstein.org.br/PDF/bsorj_America_Latina_Transformaciones_geopoliticas.pdf]</ref><ref>[SORJ, Bernardo FAUSTO, Sergio (comps.). Brasil y América del Sur: Miradas Cruzadas. Buenos Aires: Catálogos S.L.R., 2011. {{ISBN|9789508953063}}. http://www.centroedelstein.org.br/PDF/bsorj_sfausto_Brasil_y_America_del_Sur_Miradas_cruzadas.pdf]</ref><ref>[SERBIN, Andrés. Chávez, Venezuela y la reconfiguración política de América Latina y el Caribe. Buenos Aires: Siglo XXI Editora Iberoamericana, 2011. {{ISBN|9789871013913}}. http://www.centroedelstein.org.br/PDF/SERBIN_chavez_venezuela.pdf]</ref><ref>[HILB, Claudia. Silêncio, Cuba: a esquerda democrática diante do regime da Revolução Cubana. São Paulo: Paz e Terra, 2010. {{ISBN|9788577531318}}. http://www.centroedelstein.org.br/PDF/Silencio_Cuba_Sumario_Introducao.pdf]</ref><ref>[PÉCAUT, Daniel. As FARC: uma guerrilha sem fins? São Paulo: Paz e Terra, 2010. {{ISBN|9788577531288}}. http://www.centroedelstein.org.br/PDF/Farc.pdf]</ref> and '''b)''' ''Media and Democracy''.<ref>[Media and Democracy series http://www.plataformademocratica.org/English/PublicacoesPlataforma.aspx#MediosComunicacion]</ref><ref>[SORJ, Bernardo (comp.). Democracia y Medios de Comunicación. Más allá del Estado y el Mercado. Buenos Aires: Catálogos S.L.R, 2012. http://www.centroedelstein.org.br/PDF/bsorj_democracia_y_medios_de_comunicacion.pdf]</ref><ref>[SORJ, B. (comp.). Poder político y medios de comunicación - De la representación política al reality show. Buenos Aires: Siglo XXI, 2010. {{ISBN|9789871013807}}. http://www.centroedelstein.org.br/PDF/Poder_pol%C3%ADtico_y_medios.pdf]</ref>

''Plataforma Democrática'' site's includes a [[virtual library]]<ref>[Virtual Library of the Plataforma Democrática http://www.plataformademocratica.org/English/BuscaPublicacoes.aspx]</ref> of [[free access]] with 15.000 academic titles, more than hundred original papers and the book series ''The State of Democracy in Latin America''.<ref>[The State of Democracy in Latin American series http://www.plataformademocratica.org/English/PublicacoesPlataforma.aspx#EstadoDemocracia]</ref>

'''Other activities'''

The '''Edelstein Center''' did participated in the Secretariat of the [[Latin American Initiative on Drugs and Democracy]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.drogasedemocracia.org/English/Default.asp |title=Latin American Initiative on Drugs and Democracy |publisher=Drogasedemocracia.org |date= |accessdate=2012-03-14}}</ref> and of the [[Global Commission on Drug Policy]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.globalcommissionondrugs.org |title=The Global Commission on Drug Policy |publisher=Globalcommissionondrugs.org |date= |accessdate=2012-03-08}}</ref>

